    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Van Valkenburgh</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-10-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 7, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I haveto acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 22d of August.</p>
                <p>It is an occasion of satisfaction that so perfect an understanding as you
                            have described exists between the representatives of the treaty powers
                            at Yedo.</p>
                <p>The contemplated arrangement for the opening of Yedo to foreigners, and
                            of a quarter to be assigned to foreigners in the centre of the city,
                            seems to be just, and I have no reason to doubt that if carried into
                            effect on your part, will be entirely approved by the President.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. B. Van Valkenburgh,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
